  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Recent collapse of high-level US-Iran indirect talks in Islamabad on April 12 left nuclear negotiations at a standstill, with US demands for a 20-year halt on Iran's uranium enrichment rejected by Tehran as maximalist, while Iran countered with a phased approach prioritizing ceasefire and Strait of Hormuz access before nuclear issues. President Trump's April 26 statement that Iran can \"phone if it wants to talk\" underscores fragile diplomacy amid an indefinite ceasefire extension, but no new sessions are scheduled despite ongoing sanctions and ballistic missile concerns. Traders' 62.5% \"No\" consensus reflects wide gaps persisting since February Geneva rounds, with just two months until the June 30 deadline and historical JCPOA revival patterns showing such impasses rarely resolve swiftly.",
    "context_requires_regen": false,
